<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="95" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="95">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Engel" baseAuthorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megachile (Callomegachile) memecylonae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="memecylonae" subGenus="Callomegachile">Megachile (Callomegachile) memecylonae</taxonomicName>
(Engel, 2011) superficially resembles 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. (Callomegachile) atratiformis" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" rank="species" species="atratiformis" subGenus="Callomegachile">M. (Callomegachile) atratiformis</taxonomicName>
(Meade-Waldo, 1914), in overall appearance and size: large body size (18-19 mm); black body covered with black hairs throughout; yellow wings. Female is easily distinguished by mesoscutum with distinctly transverse wrinkle pattern on disc, posteriorly also with well separated punctures (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.101.1182" author="Engel, MS" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" pagination="51 - 80" refId="B20" refString="Engel, MS, Gonzalez, VH, 2011. Alocanthedon, a new subgenus of Chalicodoma from Southeast Asia (Hymenoptera, Megachilidae). ZooKeys 101: 51 - 80, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.101.1182" title="Alocanthedon, a new subgenus of Chalicodoma from Southeast Asia (Hymenoptera, Megachilidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.101.1182" volume="101" year="2011">Engel and Gonzalez 2011</bibRefCitation>
). Male can be recognized by median cell of forewings without black setae patch; juxtamandibular flange present (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Megachile (Callomegachile) memecylonae (Engel, 2011), male a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d juxtamandibular flange e basitarsi of front leg." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.997.34935.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/479643" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">14d</figureCitation>
); basitarsi of pro legs with hook shape (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Megachile (Callomegachile) memecylonae (Engel, 2011), male a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d juxtamandibular flange e basitarsi of front leg." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.997.34935.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/479643" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">14e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
